# RAG

All searches, findings, links for TREF project.

## Documentation References

### Zod
- https://zod.dev/ - Official Zod documentation
- z.infer<typeof Schema> for deriving types from schemas

### TypeScript + JSDoc
- JSDoc reference: https://www.typescriptlang.org/docs/handbook/jsdoc-supported-types.html
- checkJs in tsconfig/jsconfig enables type checking for .js files

### ESLint typescript-eslint
- https://typescript-eslint.io/ - Type-aware linting for JavaScript

### Model Context Protocol (MCP)
- https://modelcontextprotocol.io/ - Official MCP documentation
- https://modelcontextprotocol.io/docs/getting-started/intro - Introduction
- https://modelcontextprotocol.io/docs/develop/build-server - Build server guide
- npm package: @modelcontextprotocol/sdk
- McpServer class for server creation
- StdioServerTransport for stdio communication
- registerTool() with Zod schemas for input validation
- IMPORTANT: Use console.error() not console.log() in stdio servers

### Vanilla Framework (CSS)
- https://vanillaframework.io/docs - Official documentation
- CDN: https://assets.ubuntu.com/v1/vanilla_framework_version_4_38_0_min.css
- Grid: .grid-row, .grid-col-*, .grid-row--50-50, .grid-row--25-75
- Responsive grid: .grid-row--50-50-on-large, .grid-col-start-{breakpoint}{index}
- Utilities: u-hide, u-hide--small, u-no-margin, u-align--center, u-vertically-center
- Breakpoints: small (<= 620px), large (>= 1036px)

